citations:
    citation-agot-catelyn-ix:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Catelyn IX"
            text_from_source: "She found her son surrounded by his father's lords bannermen, in a drafty hall with a peat fire smoking in a black hearth … 'We need to march south to meet him.' … 'Then I will not lose,' he vowed."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Catelyn arrives at Moat Cailin, escorted by Ser Wylis and Ser Wendel Manderly (sons of Lord Wyman Manderly of White Harbor). She reunites with Robb and his army of approximately 18,000 men. Lords bannermen present: Roose Bolton, Greatjon Umber, Galbart Glover, Robett Glover, Rickard Karstark, Helman Tallhart, Lord Hornwood, Theon Greyjoy, Ser Helman Tallhart. Catelyn reports Lysa Arryn will not march — only Ser Brynden Tully (Blackfish) has come. Battle of the Golden Tooth reported: Jaime Lannister defeats Lord Vance and Lord Piper. Ser Edmure Tully captured. Riverrun under siege. Robb outlines his plan: send foot south under Roose Bolton to engage Tywin, while cavalry crosses the Green Fork at the Twins to march west to Riverrun. Catelyn counsels Roose Bolton over the Greatjon to command the eastern host."
